- 103 years old, 103 years old.

03:21.500 --> 03:22.800
Looking good.

03:22.833 --> 03:24.180
He was up
in Donnie's bocce courts

03:24.200 --> 03:27.100
faster than anybody else.

03:29.533 --> 03:32.533
Wow, that's delicious.
This is a weakness of mine.

03:32.567 --> 03:34.326
You know, they have these
street fairs in New York

03:34.333 --> 03:36.367
where they do sausage
and pepper stands.

03:36.400 --> 03:39.967
I cannot walk past one of those
things without getting them.

03:40.000 --> 03:42.633
Ohh!

03:42.667 --> 03:44.833
So how long have you
lived in this community?

03:44.867 --> 03:46.167
78 years.

03:46.200 --> 03:48.033
- So your whole life.
- Yes.

03:48.067 --> 03:50.167
Now, the first wave of
Italians who came here

03:50.200 --> 03:52.033
from Italy,
why did they come here?

03:52.067 --> 03:54.333
Did they come here
for steel jobs? Coal?

03:54.367 --> 03:57.233
Actually, trade. I think they
came here more for the trade.

03:57.267 --> 03:58.700
Yeah.

03:58.733 --> 04:01.700
Yeah, plumbers, bricklayers,
any kind of trade like that.

04:01.733 --> 04:04.300
Some Italians said that they
were told to come over here

04:04.333 --> 04:08.233
and they were gonna find
the roads paved with gold.

04:08.267 --> 04:10.967
They said, "They didn't tell us
we had to build them first."

04:11.000 --> 04:12.800
Yeah.

04:17.333 --> 04:19.466
How's the neighborhood
changed over the years?

04:19.500 --> 04:22.633
Still predominantly
Italian American, or...?

04:22.667 --> 04:24.300
Yeah, not as much as it was,

04:24.333 --> 04:26.333
but it's still more Italian
than anything else.

04:26.367 --> 04:30.400
For 35 years or so, it was
a tough time for Pittsburgh.

04:30.433 --> 04:33.667
Why did people stay?

04:33.700 --> 04:36.000
Family. Familia.

04:36.033 --> 04:37.867
I tell people,
when you come to Bloomfield,

04:37.900 --> 04:39.300
don't talk about anybody

04:39.333 --> 04:42.267
because we're
all connected somehow.

04:45.333 --> 04:46.867
- All right.
- Thank you.

04:50.167 --> 04:52.067
