at Carnegie Mellon

09:00.333 --> 09:02.133
is one of the best
in the country,

09:02.167 --> 09:04.633
inspiring an arms race
between companies

09:04.667 --> 09:06.300
looking to recruit braniacs

09:06.333 --> 09:08.800
for new fields of
artificial intelligence,

09:08.833 --> 09:10.533
cutting-edge medical research,

09:10.567 --> 09:13.300
possibly cyborg super nerds
who will no doubt

09:13.333 --> 09:15.133
revenge themselves on all of us

09:15.167 --> 09:16.867
for their painful
high school experiences

09:16.900 --> 09:20.300
by crushing us between
their synthetic mandibles.

09:20.333 --> 09:22.867
They're also good for business.

09:22.900 --> 09:24.900
- Here you go, guys.
- Thank you.

09:24.933 --> 09:26.167
Thank you.

09:26.200 --> 09:27.867
The Googlers that are coming in

09:27.900 --> 09:29.967
are coming in at
the very top of the food chain,

09:30.000 --> 09:32.400
and they're walking
into brand-new housing.

09:32.433 --> 09:34.967
They're making six figures.
They're 23 years old.

09:35.000 --> 09:37.033
- Right.
- And, you know, I think

09:37.067 --> 09:38.860
the old-school, the people
that have been here forever,

09:38.867 --> 09:40.567
are not happy about that.

09:40.600 --> 09:43.067
I mean, you know,
it's gonna be all pencil necks,

09:43.100 --> 09:46.567
like in 20 years.

09:46.600 --> 09:48.367
Bad breeding stock.

09:48.400 --> 09:50.667
It's the problem of
inclusion and exclusion, right?

09:50.700 --> 09:52.200
It's the American
problem, right?

09:52.233 --> 09:54.033
It's what Fitzgerald writes
about in "Gatsby."

09:54.067 --> 09:55.900
Who is included, who's excluded?

09:55.933 --> 09:57.900
Who's allowed in, who isn't?
Right.

09:57.933 --> 10:00.233
And that's the worry,
that we're gonna forget

10:00.267 --> 10:01.733
the people that have
lived through it,

10:01.767 --> 10:03.033
and that have stayed here,

10:03.067 --> 10:04.833
and had no choice
but to stay here.

