Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania,

14:49.600 --> 14:51.467
is a big, bright
shining star of an example

14:51.500 --> 14:55.500
of what blue collar America,
I think, was 100 years ago,

14:55.533 --> 14:58.300
When we're looking at,
like, who's applying,

14:58.333 --> 15:00.467
we also need to look
at neighborhoods.

15:00.500 --> 15:02.567
The topography
of Pittsburgh is such that,

15:02.600 --> 15:05.667
like, neighborhoods
are separated by...

15:05.700 --> 15:07.700
- Bridges.
- By bridges and ravines,

15:07.733 --> 15:10.000
and this sort of thing
means that, like,

15:10.033 --> 15:12.267
people stay
within their neighborhood.

15:13.733 --> 15:15.700
- Go.
- One.

15:15.733 --> 15:17.800
- Go.
- Two.

15:17.833 --> 15:19.800
- Go.
- Three.

15:25.667 --> 15:27.433
Up, two, good.

15:30.700 --> 15:32.133
Everybody's talking now

15:32.167 --> 15:34.033
about a Pittsburgh renaissance.

15:34.067 --> 15:35.900
You've got artists coming.

15:35.933 --> 15:38.233
There are new restaurants.

15:38.267 --> 15:40.567
Somebody's making money.
Yes.

15:40.600 --> 15:41.867
Money's definitely coming in.

15:41.900 --> 15:43.300
Is it lifting all boats?

15:43.333 --> 15:45.567
No. It is not.

15:45.600 --> 15:48.467
♪

15:48.500 --> 15:51.367
The new Pittsburgh
attracts new people,

15:51.400 --> 15:56.000
but it doesn't change the life

15:56.033 --> 15:58.133
for those workers

15:58.167 --> 16:01.967
who were left behind
and kind of spit out.

16:02.000 --> 16:03.533
This is the Hill District,

16:03.567 --> 16:06.133
traditionally African American.

16:06.167 --> 16:09.367
The numbers here do not
indicate a renaissance.

16:09.400 --> 16:11.800
Black homes
take in half the income

16:11.833 --> 16:14.900
of their white neighbors,
and African American youth

